article.headline: Saint Mary's moves on in NIT, beats Washington 85-81

images.name: Landale cleans up miss with empahtic jam
images.caption: Saint Mary's forward Jock Landale is in the right place at the right time to clean up the Emmett Naar miss with a dunk.

article.linkText: Saint Mary's moves on in NIT, beats Washington 85-81
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- Jordan Ford made a wide open 3-pointer with 45.3 seconds to go and Saint Mary's won its program-record 30th game of the season with an 85-81 victory over Washington on Monday night to reach the NIT quarterfinals. Washington freshman Jaylen Nowell answered with a deep 3 to pull to 82-79 at 33.5 but Saint Mary's worked the clock down to 12.8 before Ford sealed it with two free throws. Ford scored 22 of his 26 points in the second half. Evan Fitzner added a season-high 20 points off the bench for Saint Mary's (30-5) and Emmett Naar had 12 assists. Noah Dickerson had 22 points and nine rebounds for Washington (21-13), which lost to Saint Mary's for the first time. Matisse Thybulle moved into second in Pac-12 history for single-season steals, tying Gary Payton with 101. Thybulle's steal and fast-break dunk got Washington within 75-72 and after Saint Mary's two free throws, Dickerson spun his defender on the baseline for a two-handed dunk. ---- More AP college basketball: https://collegebasketball.ap.org; https://twitter.com/AP-Top25 and https://www.podcastone.com/ap-sports-special-events

videos.headline: Washington's Carter shows off range with deep 3
videos.description: Nahziah Carter gets the ball in transition and spots up from way behind the line, knocking down the 3 from the NIT logo.

videos.headline: Huskies' emphatic dunk cuts lead to 3
videos.description: Washington's Matisse Thybulle gets the dish on the fastbreak from David Crisp and shows off his athleticism with the high-flying slam.
